IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: Inspires and prepares young people to succeed in the global economy.
IRS990.MissionDesc: Junior Achievement of Central Illinois inspires and prepares young people to succeed in the global economy. Our volunteer-delivered, experiential programs give students knowledge and skills in financial literacy, work readiness and entrepreneurship. Junior Achievement helps to enhance the relevance of students classroom learning and increase their understanding of the value of staying in school.
IRS990.Desc: Junior Achievement of Central Illinois is part of the world's largest organization dedicated to giving young people the knowledge and skills they need to own their economic success, plan for their future, and make smart academic and economic choices. Our financial literacy, work readiness and entrepreneurship programs empower students to make a connection between what they learn in school and how it can be applied in the real world. This enhances the relevance of their classroom learning and increases their understanding of the value of staying in school.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Organization is qualified as a not-for-profit organization under Internal Revenue Code Sections 501(c)(3) and is exempt from income taxes, except on income unrelated to the Organization's charitable purposes. The Organization currently has no unrelated business income. Accordingly, no provision for income taxes has been recorded.
